I just have one thing to say about DAoC, AO, and whatever else is coming out.  I'm no expert about the newer games, so take it with a grain of salt...<br>
<br>
My premonition is that the MMORPG scene will unfold just like the FPS scene, which I think was the last cutting edge gaming explosion in the evolution of things (and brought us the 3d engine feel eq has today).  And we all know how FPS games went.  Id was the pioneer, and they owned the scene for at least 2-3 generations (wolfenstein, doom, quake, quake2... some would argue quake3 as well, but other wouldn't, so there goes total dominance).  Now that the FPS scene has matured over a few generations, now other companies are comparable.<br>
<br>
I see the Current Everquest + Kunark + Velious kinda like wolfenstein, doom, quake1, and some of quake 2.  SoL will lie around the q2/q3 stage of the comparison.  It won't be until after the DAoC/AO/SoL competition... the next generation after... that other companies actually compete for real with the original leader.  Nobody can tell at this point, everything is unreleased beta and MMORPG are very hard to tell until a real community is in place... but this is my guess...<br>
